{"title_page": "Shiva Tandava Stotra", "text_new": "{{Hindu scriptures}}\n{{Saivism}}\n'''''Shiva Tandava Stotra''''' ({{lang-sa|\u0936\u093f\u0935\u0924\u093e\u0923\u094d\u0921\u0935\u0938\u094d\u0924\u094b\u0924\u094d\u0930|\u015biva-t\u0101\u1e47\u1e0dava-stotra}}) is a ''[[stotra]]'' ([[Hinduism|Hindu]] hymn) that describes [[Shiva]]'s power and  beauty. It is traditionally attributed to [[Ravana]], the King of [[Lanka]] and devotee of Shiva.<ref>{{Cite book|last=V\u0101lm\u012bki|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aWFEAQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=ramayan+ramesh+menon&hl=en&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjxm9fwiOLoAhU3gnIEHezoBzIQ6AEwAHoECAIQAg#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=The Ramayana: A Modern Retelling of the Great Indian Epic|last2=Menon|first2=Ramesh|date=2004-05-26|publisher=Macmillan|isbn=978-0-86547-695-0|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Stotram ==\n\n<ref>{{cite book|last=Devav\u0101\u1e47\u012b-Pari\u1e63ad|title= Arv\u0101c\u012bnasa\u1e43skr\u0325tam, Volume 11, , Dill\u012b, 1989 |url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=mOQvAAAAIAAJ&q=%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%9F%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%9F%E0%A4%B5%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%9C%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%AA%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A5%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%87&dq=%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%9F%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%9F%E0%A4%B5%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%9C%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%AA%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A5%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%87&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiu687gvfboAhXxX3wKHd2gBs4Q6AEIOTAC|accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|Devanagari\n|IAST\n|-\n|\u091c\u091f\u093e\u091f\u0935\u0940\u0917\u0932\u091c\u094d\u091c\u0932\u092a\u094d\u0930\u0935\u093e\u0939\u092a\u093e\u0935\u093f\u0924\u0938\u094d\u0925\u0932\u0947\n \n\u0917\u0932\u0947\u093d\u0935\u0932\u092e\u094d\u092c\u094d\u092f \u0932\u092e\u094d\u092c\u093f\u0924